caption: Cozy place for couples or small groups. Great selection of wines. Will come again.

I've been to Gainesville Wine and Cheese a couple times before and have always had a wonderful experience. However, they put a dent in my birthday celebrations by saying they forgot someone else had booked out the whole place and there was no room for my boyfriend and I. I did receive a 40$ gift certificate but I will be taking my business elsewhere since my boyfriend works nights and we have limited time together. Make sure you call them before you go even if you have a reservation.
Amazing! And honestly the best pizza I’ve had in Gainesville.
Fantastic experience! Cant stop going back
Cute place, large variety of wines
A cozy hideaway. Friendly staff, great quality, tasty snacks!
Outstanding!!! The staff was excellent! Very helpful. This is a nice cozy place to sit and relax. It was the perfect spot for our long overdue date night!

In one of the old downtown Gainesville buildings right off of University and Main, you'll find this new little secret. Opening recently in April or May, this wine & cheese shop has what you didn't know you needed. With a very robust selection of wines, you can get lost in the moment taking in the expertise of the owner, Maude. Extremely knowledgeable, she can guide you through her diverse world of wines. The cheese selection is much smaller by comparison, but very well curated. A delicious selection of harder to find cheeses cut off the wheel or brick the old fashioned way. The shop also offers wine tastings, and when there is cooler weather, live music in the adjacent courtyard. Stop in and tell Maude hello!

Downtown wine and cheese is a great spot for a relaxing date with a bottle of wine and a cheese board on the secret patio.  The proprietor, Maude, keeps a great selection of wine ranging from very affordable to top end. Check out the wine tastings on Thursday nights.  $15 gets you 5-6 wines to taste with heavy pours. If you want to try some new wines frequently, I recommend the wine club.  There are a few different levels but I promise you will get your money's worth.  They also serve delicious pizzas on certain evenings including late night.  Come check out this awesome local spot!
Amazingly nice staff, and delicious wine and cheese! Really relaxed atmosphere and plenty of places to sit to feel privacy. Just a really cool place, my group will definitely be heading back!
To rise up.
Nice litte place. Relaxing, big selection of wines, staff was very helpful getting a good wine for my husband

Great wine tasting event! Host very enthusiast, equally so with each explanation of the different flavors in each type of wine. Loose start-time - start whenever you get there during the 2 hour window and move along at your own pace. Would have been nice to have had a written list of the wines tasted, since now I am struggling to remember the names of the my favorites. Tasting area not very big (gets crowded fast). Once done tasting, you're able to purchase glasses of wine at a discount, limited to a specific display set. One downfall: unable to purchase a charcuterie board until after tasting event ends, which loosely depends on whenever people who got there at whatever time are finished (left and got apps elsewhere).
Nice cozy place with great wine selection and helpful personnel. A few type of memberships are available with monthly wine delivery and wine tasting for two!

We were looking for a good place to enjoy some wine and a snack. Boy were we please to find it here. VERY friendly staff and had good knowledge of the wines. We selected a nice bottle of cab ordered the boat cheese. Both were great! They gave us 2 nice pieces of the cheese we couldn't eat it all with one bottle so we had to get a second one. The little garden out back was cozy and comfortable.  Good jazz was playing but not to loud. Perfect background. While we were enjoying the wine and cheese a little opossum came out and kept wandering around the plant beds. His name is Harold and he was abandoned by his mother so he is now a resident. Super cool and not afraid of people. Doesn't bother you, he just wanders around and looks cute.  When in Gainesville this will be our go to place to unwind.
It was a great place for a happy hour. Nice selection of the day's wine by the glass and we love their fig & prosciutto pizza.

honestly, felt like i was in “midnight in paris”. such an amazing and beautiful establishment. do yourself a favor and sit outside under their string lights  and feel immersed in the atmosphere. staff was so nice and helpful. would give a 7/5 stars.
Small selection of wine by glass. Food was ok.
Great staff and tastings. Reasonably priced for what is provided. Back patio and interior design is very comfortable. Love coming here
Great place with friendly knowledgeable staff. Only one A/C unit by the front tho...
I enjoyed the wine and cheese night but it was really hot when I went which made it hard to stick around for very long.
Even though it has a new owner, it remains an amazing place to go for a great bottle of wine and pizza! Legit diamond in the rough.
Best place to grab drinks and food! Cute little outdoor area and the wine tastings are so fun!
Great wine and cheese!
Love this place! Great  food, wine, and atmosphere!

It's exactly what you would expect! An adorable old house converted into a wine shop that has a great outdoor patio! The wine selection was great as well as the cheese selection. We came before dinner so we only got a small platter, but there were many options to choose from. We were here early so there was no one else here but I'm sure as the evening goes on, the patio will fill up. As we were leaving there was a jazz musician setting up to play live music! We will be back!

I have gone here twice. The first time the person behind the counter was very rude when asked about cheese recommendations. When I said we were looking for a bottle of wine he gave us all kinds of information about a $50 bottle. I then told him I was looking for something under $25 and he basically just pointed to a corner of the shop and walked away. My return visit was only because I was given a gift certificate. I was treated slightly better but the money did not go very far.
Came for the wine tasting event and had a ton of fun and learned a lot!
Great cheese.

The owner - Maude - knows her wines, knows her cheeses, can make great recommendations, has a fantastic selection of wines, cheeses, meats, fruits and jam, and kept up a conversation (since I was asking questions) during my first visit here.  For those who are fans of wine dives, or passing through Vino Volo in an airport en route to somewhere else, this was a great experience to sit down and have some wine and a cheese selection with some tasteful classical music playing in the background quietly.  While I wish the owner the kind of success that will let me come back for years to enjoy her store in peace, I also hope this stays the kind of under the radar bliss that I've just discovered, without the noisy pedestrian traffic and music drowning out the beautiful reflection that comes with savoring a variety of cheeses and wines together.
Great wines, atmosphere, and I love the events they put on. Thanks for being here!
Great wine tasting, met some nice people, great wine tasting.

I enjoyed my evening here after graduation at UF. Wine selection was nice and the owner offered her suggestions. We got one of their charcuterie boards which was plenty for 3 people to snack on. We sat outside in the garden and fortunately stopped by on a night with live jazz. It was a enjoyable and unique experience that i would recommend for date night or something to do before dinner downtown.

Solid little spot. It's a converted house that clearly has a mold issue, which I noticed as soon as the door was opened and I hadn't even stepped inside yet. But that didn't seem to bother the other patrons. To be clear, it's not just the cheeses.  It's a fine example of "Gainesville service," which isn't a shining example of the service industry. That is, if you walk over from your table and want to get another drink from the counter/vendor, there's no promises about how long that could take. One person in line doesnt mean that you can expect service anytime soon.  "Can I just grab a ______(beer) real quick?" "Sir, please wait your turn." "Oh, okay. Well, I've just been standing here for the better part of ten minutes while this woman deciphers the wine menu as if she forgot her glasses and is translating it from hieroglyphics and she's treating the ordering process as seriously as one would a retirement portfolio, whereas I've known what I want since I left a table of friends that I'd like to return to." Disgusted looks from customer service idiots.* Sheepish look from woman whose never seen a wine menu.*  I mean, if you're not asking questions or actively engaging the host for information about the menu, then it's customary to let the person behind you proceed. But here, it takes the whole 'chill vibe' well into the zone of stupid and irritating.  Food is on point, though. Very tasty. And they regularly feature solid musical duets/trios that do give it a nice atmosphere.  Neat date spot, or you're pretentious aunt from France might confuse Gainesville as a place with some culture.

Great place to stop by for a glass (or bottle) of wine and tasty snacks. Great selection and helpful staff make for a great local resource. Excellent location right downtown. Don't miss jazz nights out on the back patio.
Great place for live jazz on saturdays (weather permitting)

I love the setup of picking a bottle of wine and taking it out on their nice patio area to drink. The pizza on the weekends is very delicious too. Awesome place for date night or just people who are fans of wine and cheese.
Such a cute place! The back patio was so nice and there is a live jazz band every Saturday night! My friends and I split a few cheese items and they were all delicious

Went for their "New Years Eve dinner party" the food was horrible nobody could even eat their entree and the tiramisu was rock solid from a freezer. Plus a dj, games, and a photo booth were promised and none of those things were there. I would not waste money there again.
First time visiting. Amazing hidden gem! Love the people there and the wine! Great experience to have on a cool night out.
Great place!! Their wine tastings are a must!!
The most cozy spot in town. The recommendations and pairings are excellent. All around wonderful. And they put on the most delicious haunted house I’ve ever experienced!
The place was dirty. The service or lack thereof, was horrible. We ended up not ordering at all and walking out. I guess the bug in my water was my unappetizer.
Great place for wine tasting. Good advice for buying wine as well
Lovely ambience and outdoor seating.
Beautiful food
A good bottle of wine, a couple cheese and charcuterie plates, and an evening in the pleasant outdoor seating area is the best thing in the world.
Downtown Wine and Cheese is absolutely amazing!  I highly recommend this place!

Downtown Wine & Cheese, incorrectly listed as permanently closed by Google, is a cozy and hipster place to try a new bottle of wine paired with a tasty cheese plate or pizza. Maud, the owner, is very friendly and knowledgeable. Please help correct Google! Visit Maud and report the business as being open!

The service was so bad!  The menu states several hundred imported beers and our waiter could name two.  The menu also offered several wines of the day yet today the were "out of all red wines." I ordered the quiche of the day and the soup of the day and the waiter replied with "those won't be ready yet".... mind you it was 12:15 pm.  He went back to confirm this and then completely forgot.  His explanation for being "out" of food and drinks was because of the volume of people they had. Ummmm ok it's the beginning of August in Gainesville... what did you expect???? We also witnessed people complain about the wait for their food and the waitress got snippy with them.  People were flagging down waiters and getting up and going to the kitchen for silverware.  We were planning on ordering food but after seeing all of this we left and went somewhere else.

We happened into the Wine & Cheese Gallery because the place we were going was closed on Monday evening. The store carries a diverse and interesting wine selection and all the other accompaniments including cheeses and crackers. There was only one person working when we came in and he helped us select our wine, 1 glass each, we picked some crackers and asked for a selection of cheeses. We were the only customers in the restaurant side and our server let us know he would be dividing his time between us and the store. Service was pleasant, the atmosphere was perfect for having a great visit with friends, the wine was excellent. The price was reasonable and we felt we got our money's worth in every way. I would recommend it.
Can't beat a beautiful Friday evening on the Wine and Cheese patio.
